Vice President Biden spoke with Turkish Prime Minister Ahmet Davutoglu about the deteriorating security and humanitarian situation in northern Syria. They discussed the need for de-escalation and urged Syrian Kurdish forces to not seize additional territory near the Turkish border. The Vice President also called on Turkey to stop artillery strikes in the area. They pledged to work together to protect displaced and vulnerable populations in northwest Syria and ensure humanitarian assistance routes to Aleppo remain open. They expressed support for Turkey's fight against PKK terrorism and their shared goal of defeating ISIL. They also discussed working towards a cessation of hostilities, as agreed in Munich.